.modal.fade.introModal(id = 'tytoHelpModal', tabindex = '-1', role = 'dialog', aria-labelledby = 'tytoIntroModal', aria-hidden = 'true')
	.modal-dialog
		.modal-content
			.modal-header
				button.close(data-dismiss = "modal", aria-hidden = "true")
					|&times;
				img.modal-tyto-logo(src = "images/tyto.png")
				h4.modal-title(id = 'myModalLabel')
					|welcome to tyto!
			.modal-body
				.intro
					p
						|<strong>tyto</strong> helps you manage and organise things.
					p
						|this help dialog will only aid you in how to actually interact with tyto. For help with how to extend, customise and develop against tyto refer to the <a href ="https://github.com/jh3y/tyto">github repo</a>.
					ul
						li
							a.help-link.items(data-tyto-help-show = "items")
								|items 
						li
							a.help-link.columns(data-tyto-help-show = "columns")
								|columns
						li
							a.help-link.menu(data-tyto-help-show = "menu")
								|menu
				.help	
					.help-section.items.hide(data-tyto-help-section = "items")
						h4
							|items
						p
							|Items are draggable pieces of content that can be moved around in different columns, you can add more by using the menu or using the icon at the top of each column. You can remove an item by hitting the icon on the item.
						p
							|To edit an item;
						ul
							li
								|first put it into edit mode by double clicking it.
							li
								|then click it again to place where you want to begin editing.
							li
								|edit away
							li
								|once you are done, simply double click again or click off the item. The item will then become draggable again.
					.help-section.columns.hide(data-tyto-help-section = "columns")
						h4
							|columns
						p
							|columns simply store your items, you can edit the title of a column by simply clicking on its title. You can add new columns by using the menu and remove columns by simply clicking the icon at the top of the column you wish to remove.
					.help-section.menu.hide(data-tyto-help-section = "menu")
						h4
							|menu
						p
							|the menu can be used to add new columns and items. But it can also be used to save your current board and also load a board if you have a valid config file available. Lastly, you can use the menu to email your current board and using the config set up, the recipient and subject header can be configured.
			.modal-footer
				button.btn.btn-primary(data-dismiss = "modal", aria-hidden = "true")
					|close help.
			script.
				define(['jquery'], function () {
					$('#tytoHelpModal a.help-link').on('click', function () {
						var $this = $(this);
						$('[data-tyto-help-section]').addClass('hide');
						$('[data-tyto-help-section=' + $this.attr('data-tyto-help-show') + ']').removeClass('hide');
					});
				})	